#| "can be displayed via the menu, the shortcut <keycombo action=\"simul"
#| "\">&Ctrl;&Alt;<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo> or by double-clicking on the "
#| "tab in the tab bar. These changes can be made permanent by editing the "
#| "current profile."
msgid ""
"The name format, the remote tab title format, and the color of the current "
"tab can be changed from this dialog. The dialog can be displayed via the "
"menu, the shortcut <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Alt;<keycap>S</keycap></"
"keycombo> or by double-clicking on the tab in the tab bar. These changes are "
"temporary and can be made permanent by editing the current profile."
msgstr ""
"Le nom de l'onglet actuel est modifiable à partir de cette boîte de "
"dialogue. Elle peut être affichée par l'intermédiaire du menu, du raccourci "
"<keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Alt;<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo> ou en "
"double-cliquant sur l'onglet dans la barre d'onglets. Ces changements "
"peuvent devenir permanent en éditant le profil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1304
#, no-c-format
msgid "&konsole; will substitute these tokens for local tabs:"
msgstr "&konsole; substituera ces jetons pour les onglets locaux :"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1308
#, no-c-format
msgid "%n : program name"
msgstr "%n : nom du programme"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1309
#, no-c-format
msgid "%d : current directory (short)"
msgstr "%d : dossier actuel (court)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1310
#, no-c-format
msgid "%D : current directory (long)"
msgstr "%D : dossier actuel (long)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1311
#, no-c-format
msgid "%h : local host (short)"
msgstr "%h : hôte local (court)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1312 index.docbook:1324
#, no-c-format
msgid "%u : user name"
msgstr "%u : nom d'utilisateur"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1313
#, no-c-format
msgid "%B : user's Bourne prompt sigil ($ = normal user, # = superuser)"
msgstr ""
"%B : le symbole d'invite Bourne de l'utilisateur ($ = utilisateur normal, # "
"= superutilisateur)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1314 index.docbook:1326
#, no-c-format
msgid "%w : window title set by shell"
msgstr "%w : titre de la fenêtre tel que définie par le shell"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1315 index.docbook:1327
#, no-c-format
msgid "%# : session number"
msgstr "%# : numéro de la session"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1318
#, no-c-format
msgid "&konsole; will substitute these tokens for remote tabs:"
msgstr "&konsole; substituera ces jetons pour les onglets distants :"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1321
#, no-c-format
msgid "%c : current program"
msgstr "%c : programme actuel"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1322
#, no-c-format
msgid "%h : remote host (short)"
msgstr "%h : hôte distant (court)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1323
#, no-c-format
msgid "%H : remote host (long)"
msgstr "%H : hôte distant (long)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1325
#, no-c-format
msgid "%U : user name@ (if given)"
msgstr "%U : nom d'utilisateur (si fourni)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1331 index.docbook:1569 index.docbook:1862
#, no-c-format
msgid "Examples:"
msgstr "Exemples :"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1335
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>%d : %n</userinput> with /usr/src as current directory and "
"running <application>bash</application> will display <guibutton>src : bash</"
"guibutton>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>%d : %n</userinput> avec /usr/src comme dossier actuel dans "
"<application>bash</application> s'affichera <guibutton>src : bash</guibutton>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1342
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>%D : %n</userinput> with /usr/src as current directory and "
"running <application>top</application> will display <guibutton>/usr/src : "
"top</guibutton>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>%D : %n</userinput> avec /usr/src comme dossier actuel et en "
"exécutant <application>top</application> cela affichera <guibutton>/usr/"
"src : top</guibutton>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1349
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>%w (%#)</userinput> with ~ as current directory and running "
"<application>vim</application> in the first tab will display <guibutton>[No "
"Name] (~) - VIM(1)</guibutton>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>%w (%#)</userinput> avec ~ comme dossier actuel et en exécutant "
"<application>vim</application> dans le premier onglet, cela affichera "
"<guibutton>[Sans nom] (~) - VIM(1)</guibutton>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1363
#, no-c-format
msgid "Copy Input Dialog"
msgstr "Boîte de dialogue pour copier l'entrée"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1365
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The text entered in one tab can simultaneously be sent to other tabs. This "
"dialog allows you to select which tabs will get that input. The current tab "
"will be greyed out."
msgstr ""
"Le texte saisi dans un onglet peut être envoyé simultanément vers d'autres "
"onglets. Cette boite de dialogue vous permet de sélectionner quels onglets "
"obtiendront cette saisie. L'onglet actuel est grisé."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1387
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adjust Scrollback Dialog"
msgstr "Boîte de dialogue pour configurer l'historique"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1389
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <link linkend=\"scrollback\">scrollback</link> options for the history "
"size can be changed in this dialog. Any changes are for the current tab only "
"and will not be saved to the profile."
msgstr ""
"La taille de l'<link linkend=\"scrollback\">historique</link> peut être "
"définie dans cette boite de dialogue. Toutes les modifications seront "
"appliquées à l'onglet actuel et ne seront pas enregistrées dans le profil."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1402
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command-line Options"
msgstr "Options de ligne de commandes"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1404
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When &konsole; is started from the command line, various options can be "
"specified to modify its behavior."
msgstr ""
"Quand &konsole; est lancé depuis la ligne de commande, plusieurs options "
"peuvent être précisées pour modifier son comportement."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1409
#, no-c-format
msgid "--help"
msgstr "--help"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1410
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>List various options</action>."
msgstr "<action>Énumère les différentes options</action>."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1414
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>--profile</option> <parameter>file</parameter>"
msgstr "<option>--profile</option> <parameter>fichier</parameter>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1415
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Start &konsole;</action> using the specified profile instead of the "
"default profile."
msgstr ""
"<action>Démarre &konsole;</action> en utilisant le profil spécifié au lieu "
"de celui définit par défaut."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1420
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>--layout</option> <parameter>file</parameter>"
msgstr "<option>--layout</option> <parameter>fichier</parameter>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1421
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Start &konsole;</action> using a <link linkend=\"save-layout\">saved "
"&JSON; layout file</link>."
msgstr ""
"<action>Démarrer &konsole;</action> en utilisant un  <link linkend=\"save-"
"layout\">fichier  &JSON; enregistré de disposition</link>."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1425
#, no-c-format
msgid "--builtin-profile"
msgstr "--builtin-profile"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1426
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use the built-in profile instead of the current default profile."
msgstr "Utiliser le profil intégré au lieu de celui défini par défaut."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1430
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>--workdir</option> <parameter>dir</parameter>"
msgstr "<option>--workdir</option> <parameter>dossier</parameter>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1431
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Open with</action> <parameter>dir</parameter> as the initial working "
"directory."
msgstr ""
"<action>Démarre avec</action> le <parameter>dossier</parameter> comme "
"emplacement de travail initial."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1436
#, no-c-format
msgid "--hold, --noclose"
msgstr "--hold, --noclose"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1437
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Do not close</action> the initial session automatically when it ends."
msgstr ""
"<action>Ne ferme pas</action> automatiquement la session initiale quand elle "
"s'arrête."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1442
#, no-c-format
msgid "--new-tab"
msgstr "--new-tab"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1443
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Create a new tab</action> in an existing window rather than creating "
"a new window."
msgstr ""
"<action>Créé un nouvel onglet</action> dans une fenêtre existante plutôt que "
"d'en créer une nouvelle."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1448
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>--tabs-from-file </option><parameter>file</parameter>"
msgstr "<option>--tabs-from-file </option><parameter>fichier</parameter>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1449
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Create tabs</action> as specified in the given tabs configuration "
"file."
msgstr ""
"<action>Créé des onglets</action> tels que définis dans un fichier de "
"configuration des onglets."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1451
#, no-c-format
msgid "The file has one tab per line in the following format:"
msgstr ""
"Ce fichier contient un onglet par ligne et se présente sous ce format :"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1452
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each line specifies a tab to open using up to 4 fields specifying how it is "
"to open. Fields are delimited with <userinput>;;</userinput> and a field "
"name must have a <userinput>:</userinput> appended. Empty lines or lines "
"with <userinput>#</userinput> at the beginning are ignored, so you can use "
"line beginning with <userinput>#</userinput> to add comments."
msgstr ""
"Chaque ligne spécifie un onglet à ouvrir à l'aide de quatre champs "
"déterminant la procédure. Ces champs sont délimités avec <userinput>;;</"
"userinput>, en plus de l'ajout de <userinput>:</userinput> au nom du champ. "
"Les lignes vides ou commençant par <userinput>#</userinput> sont ignorées, "
"ainsi vous pourrez introduire des commentaires en ajoutant <userinput>#</"
"userinput> en début de ligne."

#. Tag: member
#: index.docbook:1459
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>title:</userinput> a name for this tab, tab default if blank or "
"not specified"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>title:</userinput> un nom pour l'onglet, la valeur par défaut "
"sera utilisée si ce champ est vide ou absent"

#. Tag: member
#: index.docbook:1460
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>workdir:</userinput> working directory, <filename class="
"\"directory\"> ~</filename> if blank or not specified"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>workdir:</userinput> dossier de travail, <filename class="
"\"directory\"> ~</filename> si vide ou absent"

#. Tag: member
#: index.docbook:1461
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>profile:</userinput> a &konsole; profile to use, the default if "
"blank or not specified"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>profile:</userinput> un profil &konsole; à employer, celui par "
"défaut si vide ou absent"

#. Tag: member
#: index.docbook:1462
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput>command:</userinput> a command to run"
msgstr "<userinput>command:</userinput> une commande à exécuter"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each line should contain at least one of <userinput>command</userinput> or "
"<userinput>profile</userinput> field."
msgstr ""
"Chaque ligne devra contenir au moins un champ <userinput>command</userinput> "
"ou <userinput>profile</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1466
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Example: <userinput>title: %n;; command: /usr/bin/top ;; profile: Shell</"
"userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Exemple : <userinput>title: %n;; command: /usr/bin/top ;; profile: Terminal</"
"userinput>"

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1472
#, no-c-format
msgid "--background-mode"
msgstr "--background-mode"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1473
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Start &konsole;</action> in the background and bring to the front "
"when <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Shift;<keycap>F12</keycap></keycombo> "
"(by default) is pressed."
msgstr ""
"<action>Démarre &konsole;</action> en arrière plan et l'affiche lorsque la "
"combinaison <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Maj;<keycap>F12</keycap></"
"keycombo> (par défaut) est saisie."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1478
#, no-c-format
msgid "--separate"
msgstr "--separate"

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1479
#, no-c-format
msgid "--nofork"
msgstr "--nofork"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1480
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Run</action> the new instance of &konsole; in a separate process."
msgstr ""
"<action>Lance</action> une nouvelle instance de &konsole; dans un processus "
"séparé."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1485
#, no-c-format
msgid "--show-menubar"
msgstr "--show-menubar"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1486
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Show</action> the menubar, overriding the default behavior."
msgstr ""
"<action>Affiche</action> la barre de menus en ignorant le comportement par "
"défaut."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1491
#, no-c-format
msgid "--hide-menubar"
msgstr "--hide-menubar"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1492
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Hide</action> the menubar, overriding the default behavior."
msgstr ""
"<action>Cache</action> la barre de menus en ignorant le comportement par "
"défaut."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1497
#, no-c-format
msgid "--show-tabbar"
msgstr "--show-tabbar"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1498
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Show</action> the tabbar, overriding the default behavior."
msgstr ""
"<action>Affiche</action> la barre des onglets en ignorant le comportement "
"par défaut."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1503
#, no-c-format
msgid "--hide-tabbar"
msgstr "--hide-tabbar"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1504
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Hide</action> the tabbar, overriding the default behavior."
msgstr ""
"<action>Cache</action> la barre des onglets en ignorant le comportement par "
"défaut."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1509
#, no-c-format
msgid "--fullscreen"
msgstr "--fullscreen"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1510
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Start &konsole; in fullscreen mode</action>."
msgstr "<action>Démarre &konsole; en mode plein-écran</action>."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1514
#, no-c-format
msgid "--notransparency"
msgstr "--notransparency"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1515
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Disable</action> transparent backgrounds, even if the system "
"supports them."
msgstr ""
"<action>Désactive</action> les fonds transparents, même si le système les "
"prends en charge."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1520
#, no-c-format
msgid "--list-profiles"
msgstr "--list-profiles"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1521
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>List</action> all available profiles."
msgstr "<action>Liste</action> tous les profils disponibles."

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1526
#, no-c-format
msgid "--list-profile-properties"
msgstr "--list-profile-properties"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1528
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>List</action> all possible properties with name and type. See option "
"<option>-p</option>."
msgstr ""
"<action>Répertorier</action> toutes les propriétés possibles avec leur nom "
"et type. Veuillez voir l'option <option>-p</option>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1530
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "For more information, please visit <ulink url=\"http://api.kde.org/4.x-"
#| "api/kde-baseapps-apidocs/konsole/html/classKonsole_1_1Profile."
#| "html#a57848e15fe69d3f27565851fe7cda429\">&konsole; API Reference</ulink>."
msgid ""
"For more information, please visit <ulink url=\"https://api.kde.org/4.14-api/"
"applications-apidocs/konsole/html/classKonsole_1_1Profile.html\">&konsole; "
"API Reference</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Pour plus d'informations, veuillez consulter le <ulink url=\"http://api.kde."
"org/4.x-api/kde-baseapps-apidocs/konsole/html/classKonsole_1_1Profile."
"html#a57848e15fe69d3f27565851fe7cda429\">Référentiel API de &konsole;</"
"ulink>."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1539
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-p</option> <parameter>property=value</parameter>"
msgstr "<option>-p</option> <parameter>propriété=valeur</parameter>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1540
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Change</action> the value of a profile property."
msgstr "<action>Modifie</action> la valeur d'une propriété du profil."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1545
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-e</option> <parameter>command</parameter>"
msgstr "<option>-e</option> <parameter>commande</parameter>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1546
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<action>Execute</action> <parameter>command</parameter> instead of the "
"normal shell."
msgstr ""
"<action>Exécute</action> une <parameter>commande</parameter> au lieu de "
"l'interpréteur de commandes habituel."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1548
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option will catch all following arguments passed to &konsole;, and "
"execute it as <parameter>command</parameter>. So this option should always "
"be used as the last option."
msgstr ""
"Cette option reçoit tous les arguments suivants pour les exécuter en tant "
"que <parameter>commande</parameter>, sans les passés à &konsole;. Ainsi, "
"cette option devrait toujours être la dernière employée."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1554
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "&konsole; also accepts generic &Qt; and &kde; options:"
msgid ""
"&konsole; also accepts generic &Qt; and &kf6-full; options, see man pages "
"qt6options and kf6options."
msgstr "&konsole; accepte aussi les options génériques de &Qt; et de &kde; :"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1559
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scripting &konsole;"
msgstr "Script pour &konsole;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1561
#, no-c-format
msgid "&konsole; does support numerous methods that can be used with &DBus;."
msgstr ""
"&konsole; prend en charge de multiples méthodes pouvant être utilisées avec "
"&DBus;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1563
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are two ways to use the &DBus; interface: &Qt;'s &GUI; "
"<application>qdbusviewer</application> and the command line "
"<application>qdbus</application>."
msgstr ""
"Il existe deux manières d'utiliser l'interface &DBus; : l'interface "
"graphique pour &Qt; <application>qdbusviewer</application> ou la ligne de "
"commande <application>qdbus</application>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1573
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> will display all services "
"available."
msgstr ""
"<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> affichera tous les "
"services disponibles."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1579
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>org.kde.konsole</"
"option> will display the &DBus; interface for &konsole;."
msgstr ""
"<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>org.kde.konsole</"
"option> affichera l'interface &DBus; pour &konsole;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1586
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>org.kde.konsole /"
"Windows/1</option> will display methods for controlling window 1."
msgstr ""
"<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>org.kde.konsole /"
"Windows/1</option> affichera les méthodes pour contrôler la fenêtre 1."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1594
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>org.kde."
#| "konsole /Windows/1</option> will display methods for controlling window 1."
msgid ""
"<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>org.kde.konsole "
"$KONSOLE_DBUS_WINDOW</option> will display methods for controlling the "
"current window."
msgstr ""
"<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>org.kde.konsole /"
"Windows/1</option> affichera les méthodes pour contrôler la fenêtre 1."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1601
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>org.kde.konsole /"
"Sessions/1</option> will display methods for controlling session 1."
msgstr ""
"<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>org.kde.konsole /"
"Session/1</option> affichera les méthodes pour contrôler la session 1."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1608
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>org.kde."
#| "konsole /Sessions/1</option> will display methods for controlling session "
#| "1."
msgid ""
"<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>org.kde.konsole "
"$KONSOLE_DBUS_SESSION</option> will display methods for controlling the "
"current session."
msgstr ""
"<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>org.kde.konsole /"
"Session/1</option> affichera les méthodes pour contrôler la session 1."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1615
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>org.kde."
#| "konsole /Sessions/1</option> will display methods for controlling session "
#| "1."
msgid ""
"<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>"
"$KONSOLE_DBUS_SERVICE $KONSOLE_DBUS_SESSION</option> will display methods "
"for controlling the current &konsole;'s session."
msgstr ""
"<prompt>&percnt;</prompt> <command>qdbus</command> <option>org.kde.konsole /"
"Session/1</option> affichera les méthodes pour contrôler la session 1."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1625
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If any of the above commands outputs: Service 'org.kde.konsole' does not "
"exist, change <option>org.kde.konsole</option> to one of the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1632
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<option>org.kde.konsole-`pidof -s konsole`</option> (will select first pid)"
msgstr ""
"<option>org.kde.konsole-`pidof -s konsole` </option> (Sélectionnera le "
"premier « PID »)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1636
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<option>$KONSOLE_DBUS_SERVICE</option> (this can be used from the current "
"&konsole;)"
msgstr ""
"<option>$KONSOLE_DBUS_SERVICE</option> (Cela peut être utilisé à partir de "
"l'instance courante de &konsole;)"

#. Tag: option
#: index.docbook:1641
#, no-c-format
msgid "select one from the output of 'qdbus | grep konsole'"
msgstr "Sélectionnez-en un dans la sortie de « qdbus | grep konsole »."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1647
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "For more information, please visit <ulink url=\"http://techbase.kde.org/"
#| "Development/Tutorials/D-Bus/Introduction\">&DBus; tutorial</ulink>."
msgid ""
"For more information, please visit <ulink url=\"https://techbase.kde.org/"
"Development/Tutorials/D-Bus/Introduction\">&DBus; tutorial</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Pour obtenir plus d'informations, voyez ce <ulink url=\"http://techbase.kde."
"org/Development/Tutorials/D-Bus/Introduction\">tutoriel sur &DBus;</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1655
#, no-c-format
msgid "Terminal Key Bindings"
msgstr "Combinaisons de touches pour le terminal"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1658
#, no-c-format
msgid "How &konsole; Uses Key Bindings"
msgstr "Comment &konsole; utilise les combinaisons de touches"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1662
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&konsole; uses *.keytab files to translate key combinations into control "
"characters and escape sequences that are sent to the shell or to interactive "
"programs (typically programs that use the Alternate Screen buffer, &eg; "
"<application>vim</application>, <application>less</application>, "
"<application>screen</application>) running in the shell."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1664
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Users can customize the key bindings settings in &konsole; using the Key "
"Bindings Editor. A key combination can be configured to send a specific "
"control or escape sequence to the terminal."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1666
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can open the Key Bindings Editor from the menu entry "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>Edit Current Profile</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>, and going to the <guilabel>Keyboard</guilabel> "
"tab. Listed there are the Key Bindings schemas that come by default with "
"&konsole;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1670
#, no-c-format
msgid "Key Combinations and Modes"
msgstr "Modes et combinaisons de touches"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1672
#, no-c-format
msgid "Key combinations follow the pattern:"
msgstr "Les combinaisons de touches suivent le modèle :"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1673
#, no-c-format
msgid "Key (+|-) Modes"
msgstr "Modes avec touches (+ | -)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1676
#, no-c-format
msgid "for example:"
msgstr "par exemple :"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1677
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Up+Shift+AppScreen\n"
"Down+Shift-AppScreen\n"
"Space+Ctrl"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1680
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Key names are defined in the qnamespace.h header file, with the <quote>Qt::"
"Key_</quote> prefix removed, for a list of key names check the <ulink url="
"\"https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qt.html#Key-enum\">Qt::Key enumeration in the &Qt; "
"documentation</ulink>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1682
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <quote>+</quote> preceding a Mode name means that mode is <emphasis>set</"
"emphasis>; for a modifier key, that means it's pressed, whereas for all "
"other modes it means that particular mode is in effect (&ie; active). For "
"example <quote>+Ctrl</quote> means the key combination will work only if the "
"&Ctrl; key is pressed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1684
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <quote>-</quote> preceding a Mode name means that mode is <emphasis>reset</"
"emphasis>; basically this is the opposite of putting <quote>+</quote> before "
"a Mode name, so for a modifier key that means the key isn't pressed, whereas "
"for all other modes it means that particular mode is inactive. For example "
"<quote>-Ctrl</quote> means the key combination will work only if the &Ctrl; "
"key is <emphasis>not</emphasis> pressed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1687
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a Mode name isn't present in a key combination, its state is ignored."
msgstr ""
"Si un nom de mode est absent dans une combinaison de clés, son état est "
"ignoré."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1690
#, no-c-format
msgid "The supported Key Bindings modes are listed below:"
msgstr ""
"Les modes de combinaisons de touches pris en charge sont énumérés ci-"
"dessous :"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1695
#, no-c-format
msgid "Alt, Ctrl, Shift"
msgstr "ALT, CTRL, Màj"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1697
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One or more of these Modes can be used in a key combination, if any of them "
"is set, the key combination uses that modifier key, respectively; and vice "
"versa if it's reset"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1702
#, no-c-format
msgid "AnyModifier"
msgstr "AnyModifier"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1704
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this mode is set, the key combination uses any modifier key (any of the "
"previous three modifier keys); and vice versa if it's reset"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1709
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ansi"
msgstr "ANSI"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1711
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this mode is set, &konsole; will send ANSI escape and control sequences"
msgstr ""
"Si ce mode est défini, &konsole; enverra des séquences « ANSI » "
"d'échappement et de contrôle"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1712
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this mode is reset &konsole; will send VT52 escape and control sequences"
msgstr ""
"Si ce mode est réinitialisé, &konsole; enverra des séquences « VT52 » "
"d'échappement et de contrôle"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1717
#, no-c-format
msgid "AppScreen"
msgstr "AppScreen"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1719
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this mode is set, the key combination will only affect interactive "
"programs that use the Alternate Screen buffer"
msgstr ""
"Si ce mode est défini, la combinaison de touches n'affectera que les "
"programmes interactifs utilisant le tampon alternatif d'écran."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1720
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this mode is reset the key combination will only affect the terminal when "
"it's using the Normal Screen buffer"
msgstr ""
"Si ce mode est réinitialisé, la combinaison de touches n'affectera le "
"terminal que lorsqu'il utilise le tampon d'écran normal"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1723
#, no-c-format
msgid "&konsole; makes use of two screen buffers:"
msgstr "&konsole; utilise deux tampons d'écran :"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1726
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Normal Screen buffer (default): allows you to scroll back to view "
"previous lines of output, this is the default buffer you usually use to "
"execute commands... &etc;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1729
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Alternate Screen buffer: the terminal switches to this buffer when you "
"run an interactive program (&eg; <application>less</application>, "
"<application>vim</application>, <application>screen</application>, "
"<application>tmux</application>... &etc;)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1738
#, no-c-format
msgid "KeyPad"
msgstr "Pavé numérique"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1740
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this mode is set, the key combination uses a key on the Keypad (Number "
"Pad). This mode is useful to distinguish between keys on the keyboard and "
"keys on the Keypad. For example when Num Lock is <emphasis>on</emphasis> you "
"can configure two separate key combinations, one using the key labelled "
"<quote>1</quote> on the keyboard (usually under the <keycap>F1</keycap> key) "
"and the other using the key labelled <quote>1</quote> on the Keypad. The "
"same concept applies when Num Lock is <emphasis>off</emphasis> for the End, "
"Home, Cursor Keys ...etc on the Keypad"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1745
#, no-c-format
msgid "AppCursorKeys"
msgstr "AppCursorKeys"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1747
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This mode implements the VT100 <ulink url=\"https://www.vt100.net/docs/vt100-"
"ug/chapter3.html#DECCKM\">Cursor Keys Mode (DECCKM)</ulink>. It controls the "
"escape sequences each Cursor Key (<keycap>Up</keycap>, <keycap>Down</"
"keycap>, <keycap>Right</keycap>, <keycap>Left</keycap>) sends, depending on "
"whether this mode is set or reset"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1748
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default &konsole; follows the XTerm behavior of treating the "
"<keycap>Home</keycap> and <keycap>End</keycap> keys as cursor keys with "
"respect to DECCKM"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1753
#, no-c-format
msgid "AppKeyPad"
msgstr "AppKeyPad"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1755
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this mode is set, the key combination will only work when the Keypad is "
"in Application Mode (DECKPAM)"
msgstr ""
"Si ce mode est défini, la combinaison de touches ne fonctionnera que lorsque "
"le clavier est en mode « Application » (DECKPAM)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1756
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this mode is reset, the key combination will only work when the Keypad is "
"in Numeric Mode (DECKPNM)"
msgstr ""
"Si ce mode est réinitialisé, la combinaison de touches ne fonctionnera que "
"lorsque le clavier est en mode numérique (DECKPNM)"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:1761
#, no-c-format
msgid "NewLine"
msgstr "Saut de ligne"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1763
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this mode is set, the <keycap>Return</keycap> (Enter) key on the keyboard "
"will send both Carriage Return \"\\r\" and New Line \"\\n\" control "
"characters"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1764
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this mode is reset, the <keycap>Return</keycap> key will send only a "
"Carriage Return \"\\r\""
msgstr ""
"Si ce mode est réinitialisé, la touche <keycap>Entrée</keycap> enverra "
"uniquement un retour en chariot (CR) « \\r »"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1765
#, no-c-format
msgid "The same applies to the <keycap>Enter</keycap> key on the Keypad"
msgstr ""
"Il en va de même pour la touche <keycap>Entrée</keycap> du pavé numérique."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1766
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This mode emulates the <ulink url=\"https://www.vt100.net/docs/vt100-ug/"
"chapter3.html#LNM\">LNM - Line Feed/New Line Mode</ulink>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1772
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that each combination of Key and Modes (set/reset) must be unique. For "
"example, consider the following two rules:"
msgstr ""
"Veuillez noter que chaque combinaison de touches et de modes (définition / "
"réinitialisation) doit être unique. Par exemple, veuillez prendre en compte "
"les deux règles suivantes :"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1775
#, no-c-format
msgid "A+Shift : <quote>A</quote>"
msgstr "A + Màj : <quote>A</quote>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1776
#, no-c-format
msgid "a : <quote>a</quote>"
msgstr "a : <quote>a</quote>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1778
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&konsole; will <emphasis>not</emphasis> accept the small letter <quote>a</"
"quote> rule, you have to add a <quote>-Shift</quote> to that rule to make it "
"work."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1782
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Output Field"
msgstr "Le champ de sortie"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1784
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the Output field you can add the escape sequences or control characters "
"that you want &konsole; to send to the terminal when the associated key "
"combination is pressed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1786
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also use any of the following keywords, each of which has a special "
"meaning in &konsole;:"
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez également utiliser l'un des mots clés suivants, chacun ayant une "
"signification particulière dans &konsole; :"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1789
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"scrollUpLine : scroll up one line in the shell history scrollback buffer"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1790
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"scrollUpPage : scroll up one page in the shell history scrollback buffer"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1791
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"scrollDownLine : scroll down one line in the shell history scrollback buffer"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1792
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"scrollDownPage : scroll down one page in the shell history scrollback buffer"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1793
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"scrollUpToTop : scroll up to the begining of the shell history scrollback "
"buffer"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1794
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"scrollDownToBottom : scroll down to the end of the shell history scrollback "
"buffer"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1797
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also use strings with C-string syntax; you may use the following "
"escapes sequences:"
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez également utiliser des chaines avec la syntaxe des chaines du "
"langage C. Vous pouvez utiliser les séquences d'échappement suivantes:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1800
#, no-c-format
msgid "\\E : Escape"
msgstr "\\E : Échap"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1801
#, no-c-format
msgid "\\\\ : Backslash"
msgstr "\\\\ : barre oblique inverse"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1802
#, no-c-format
msgid "\\\" : Double quote"
msgstr "\\\" : double guillemet"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1803
#, no-c-format
msgid "\\t : Tab"
msgstr "\\t : tabulation"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1804
#, no-c-format
msgid "\\r : Carriage Return"
msgstr "\\r : retour chariot"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1805
#, no-c-format
msgid "\\n : New line"
msgstr "\\n : saut de ligne"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1806
#, no-c-format
msgid "\\b : Backspace"
msgstr "\\b : retour en arrière"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1808
#, no-c-format
msgid "\\xHH : where HH are two hex digits"
msgstr "\\xHH : où HH sont deux caractères hexadécimaux"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1810
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This can be used to send &ASCII; control characters, &eg; <quote>\\x00</"
"quote> which is the NUL character"
msgstr ""
"Ceci peut être utilisé pour envoyer des caractères &ASCII;, de contrôle, "
"&pex; <quote>\\x00</quote>,représentant le caractère « NULL »"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1818
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other System Resources"
msgstr "Autres ressources du système"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1819
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are other system resources that can affect terminal Key Bindings:"
msgstr ""
"Il existe d'autres ressources du système pouvant affecter les combinaisons "
"de touches du terminal :"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1822
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Consult the <ulink url=\"man:terminfo(5)\">terminfo</ulink> or <ulink url="
"\"man:termcap(5)\">termcap</ulink> database for the expected escape "
"sequences and control characters that each key combination is supposed to "
"send."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1825
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is likely that your system has other keyboard databases which have to be "
"in sync too, (&eg; <ulink url=\"man:bash(1)\">/etc/inputrc and readline</"
"ulink> for the <application>BASH shell</application>) as they affect the "
"operations (interactions) bound to key combinations."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1831
#, no-c-format
msgid "Further Reading"
msgstr "Lectures complémentaires "

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1832
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information on escape sequences and control characters, check the "
"following documentation:"
msgstr ""
"Pour plus d'informations sur les séquences d'échappement et les caractères "
"de contrôle, veuillez consulter la documentation suivante :"

#. Tag: ulink
#: index.docbook:1835
#, no-c-format
msgid "The VT100 user guide"
msgstr "Le manuel utilisateur pour VT100"

#. Tag: ulink
#: index.docbook:1838
#, no-c-format
msgid "The VT102 user guide"
msgstr "Le manuel utilisateur pour VT102"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1841
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The comprehensive and indispensable <ulink url=\"https://invisible-island."
"net/xterm/ctlseqs/ctlseqs.html\">XTerm Control Sequences</ulink> "
"documentation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1850
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using Style Sheet for the Tab Bar"
msgstr "Employé une feuille de style pour la barre d'onglets"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1851
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default style sheet for the tab bar sets the minimum and maximum tab "
"widths. The user can create a <filename role=\"extension\">.css</filename> "
"file and have &konsole; use that as the style sheet for the tab bar. In the "
"<filename role=\"extension\">.css</filename> file, the widget to use is "
"<userinput>QTabBar::tab</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"La feuille de style par défaut pour la barre des onglets définie la largeur "
"minimale et maximale des onglets. L'utilisateur peut créer un fichier "
"<filename role=\"extension\">.css</filename> que &konsole; utilisera pour "
"habiller la barre d'onglets. Dans le fichier <filename role=\"extension\">."
"css</filename>, le composant graphique à utiliser est <userinput>QTabBar::"
"tab</userinput>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1857
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information, consider reading <ulink url=\"https://doc.qt.io/qt-5/"
"stylesheet.html\">&Qt; Style Sheets</ulink>"
msgstr ""
"Pour plus d'informations, veuillez consulter la <ulink url=\"https://doc.qt."
"io/qt-5/stylesheet.html\">page des feuilles de style sous &Qt;</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1870
#, no-c-format
msgid "Change the selected tab's background to a light gray"
msgstr "Colorer l'arrière-plan de l'onglet sélectionné en gris clair"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1872
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"QTabBar::tab:selected {\n"
"    background: #999999\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"QTabBar::tab:selected {\n"
"    background: #999999\n"
"}"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1876
#, no-c-format
msgid "Change the selected tab's text to red"
msgstr "Colorer le texte de l'onglet sélectionné en rouge"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1878
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"QTabBar::tab:selected {\n"
"    color: red\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"QTabBar::tab:selected {\n"
"    color: red\n"
"}"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1881
#, no-c-format
msgid "All tabs will be at least 200 pixels in width"
msgstr "Tous les onglets feront au moins 200 pixels de large"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1883
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"QTabBar::tab {\n"
"    min-width: 200px\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"QTabBar::tab {\n"
"    min-width: 200px\n"
"}"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1886
#, no-c-format
msgid "Only the selected tab will be at least 200 pixels in width"
msgstr "Seul l'onglet sélectionné fera au moins 200 pixels de large"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1888
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"QTabBar::tab::selected {\n"
"    min-width: 200px\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"QTabBar::tab::selected {\n"
"    min-width: 200px\n"
"}"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1891
#, no-c-format
msgid "Any of these can be combined in one file"
msgstr "Et le tout combiné dans un seul fichier"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1893
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"QTabBar::tab::selected {\n"
"    background: #999999;\n"
"    color: red;\n"
"    min-width: 200px;\n"
"}\n"
"QTabBar::tab {\n"
"    min-width: 100px\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"QTabBar::tab::selected {\n"
"    background: #999999;\n"
"    color: red;\n"
"    min-width: 200px;\n"
"}\n"
"QTabBar::tab {\n"
"    min-width: 100px\n"
"}"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1903
#, no-c-format
msgid "Did You Know?, Common Issues and More"
msgstr "Le saviez-vous, problèmes courants et plus"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1906
#, no-c-format
msgid "Did You Know?"
msgstr "Le saviez-vous ?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1910
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Pressing &Ctrl; while selecting text will cause lines breaks to be converted "
"to spaces when pasted."
msgstr ""
"Appuyer sur &Ctrl; tout en sélectionnant du texte permet de convertir les "
"retours à la ligne en espaces lors d'un copier-coller."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1914
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Pressing the <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Alt;</keycombo> keys while "
"selecting text will select columns."
msgstr ""
"Utiliser les touches <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Alt;</keycombo> tout "
"en désignant du texte sélectionnera les colonnes."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1918
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<mousebutton>Wheel</mousebutton></"
"keycombo> combination will zoom text size, like in konqueror and firefox."
msgstr ""
"La combinaison <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<mousebutton>Molette</"
"mousebutton></keycombo> modifiera la taille de la police, comme dans "
"Konqueror et Firefox."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1922
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a program evaluates either mouse button, pressing the &Shift; key will "
"allow the popup menu to appear."
msgstr ""
"Quand un programme prend le contrôle d'un des boutons de la souris, appuyez "
"sur &Maj; pour permettre au menu contextuel d'apparaitre."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1926
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Shift;<keycap>F10</keycap></keycombo> "
"shortcut will activate the menu."
msgstr ""
"Le raccourci <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Maj;<keycap>F10</keycap></"
"keycombo> activera le menu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1930
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Shift;<keycap>Insert</keycap></keycombo> "
"keys will insert the clipboard."
msgstr ""
"Les touches <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Maj;<keycap>Inser</keycap></"
"keycombo> inséreront le contenu du presse-papiers."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1934
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Double-clicking will select a whole word. Continuing to hold the mouse "
"button and moving the mouse will extend the selection."
msgstr ""
"Un double-clic sélectionne un mot ; en maintenant le bouton enfoncé tout en "
"déplaçant la souris, vous étendrez la sélection."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1938
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Triple-clicking will select a whole line. Continuing to hold the mouse "
"button and moving the mouse will extend the selection."
msgstr ""
"Un triple-clic sélectionne une ligne entière ; en maintenant le bouton "
"enfoncé tout en déplaçant la souris, vous étendrez la sélection."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1942
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "There is a hidden feature for the \"%d\" formatter in tab title. You can "
